        "passed": false,
        "feedback": "The generated L-bracket fails because the holes in the vertical wall do not go all the way through. In CadQuery, the 'XZ' Workplane has its normal pointing in the -Y direction. As a result, `.workplane(offset=wall_thickness/2.0)` moves the cutting cylinder's center to Y = -2. A cylinder of length 10 centered at Y = -2 only extends to Y = +3. Since the wall spans from Y = 0 to Y = 4, the cylinder only cuts 3mm deep into the back of the wall, creating blind holes rather than the requested through-holes. This is confirmed by the lack of visible holes on the front of the wall in the isometric render, and the exact volume metric being 14056 mm³ (which perfectly matches a 3mm depth cut per hole instead of the required 4mm). To fix this, either use a much longer cylinder that guarantees intersection (e.g., `cylinder(20.0, ...)`) without shifting the offset, or use a more robust topological approach by selecting the face: `bracket.faces('>Y').workplane().pushPoints([(-12, 19-4), (12, 19-4)]).hole(wall_hole_dia)`.",
